-- Alitalia receives offers for maintenance, cargo
-- 
-- Fri Sep 12, 2008 9:24am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/12/us-alitalia-offers-idUSRAT00401220080912

 

 ROME  (Reuters) - Alitalia's AZPIa.MI bankruptcy commissioner has received expressions of interest for the airline's heavy maintenance and cargo units, the bankrupt airline said in a statement. 

 Aviation Management Consulting GmBH &Co. expressed interest in buying the airline's heavy maintenance operations including its Atitech unit, while Alis-Aerolinee Italiane and Miro Radici Finance expressed interest in buy the airline's cargo unit, Alitalia said. The bankruptcy commissioner has asked both for further details to evaluate their interest. (Reporting by  Deepa Babington )